\title{Modal}

\taxon{skill}

\meta{description}{Run Python code in the cloud with serverless containers, GPUs, and autoscaling. Use when deploying ML models, running batch processing jobs, scheduling compute-intensive tasks, or serving APIs that require GPU acceleration or dynamic scaling.}

\subtree{
\title{Modal}
\subtree{
\title{Overview}
\p{Modal is a serverless platform for running Python code in the cloud with minimal configuration. Execute functions on powerful GPUs, scale automatically to thousands of containers, and pay only for compute used.}

\pre{\startverb
Modal is particularly suited for AI/ML workloads, high-performance batch processing, scheduled jobs, GPU inference, and serverless APIs. Sign up for free at https://modal.com and receive $30/month in credits.
\stopverb}
}

\subtree{
\title{When to Use This Skill}
\p{Use Modal for:}

\ul{
\li{Deploying and serving ML models (LLMs, image generation, embedding models)}
\li{Running GPU-accelerated computation (training, inference, rendering)}
\li{Batch processing large datasets in parallel}
\li{Scheduling compute-intensive jobs (daily data processing, model training)}
\li{Building serverless APIs that need automatic scaling}
\li{Scientific computing requiring distributed compute or specialized hardware}
}
}

\subtree{
\title{Authentication and Setup}
\p{Modal requires authentication via API token.}

\subtree{
\title{Initial Setup}
\pre{\startverb
# Install Modal
uv uv pip install modal

# Authenticate (opens browser for login)
modal token new
\stopverb}

\p{This creates a token stored in \code{\startverb ~/.modal.toml\stopverb}. The token authenticates all Modal operations.}
}

\subtree{
\title{Verify Setup}
\pre{\startverb
import modal

app = modal.App("test-app")

@app.function()
def hello():
    print("Modal is working!")
\stopverb}

\p{Run with: \code{\startverb modal run script.py\stopverb}}
}
}

\subtree{
\title{Core Capabilities}
\p{Modal provides serverless Python execution through Functions that run in containers. Define compute requirements, dependencies, and scaling behavior declaratively.}

\subtree{
\title{1. Define Container Images}
\p{Specify dependencies and environment for functions using Modal Images.}

\pre{\startverb
import modal

# Basic image with Python packages
image = (
    modal.Image.debian_slim(python_version="3.12")
    .uv_pip_install("torch", "transformers", "numpy")
)

app = modal.App("ml-app", image=image)
\stopverb}

\p{\strong{Common patterns:}}

\ul{
\li{Install Python packages: \code{\startverb .uv_pip_install("pandas", "scikit-learn")\stopverb}}
\li{Install system packages: \code{\startverb .apt_install("ffmpeg", "git")\stopverb}}
\li{Use existing Docker images: \code{\startverb modal.Image.from_registry("nvidia/cuda:12.1.0-base")\stopverb}}
\li{Add local code: \code{\startverb .add_local_python_source("my_module")\stopverb}}
}

\p{See \code{\startverb references/images.md\stopverb} for comprehensive image building documentation.}
}

\subtree{
\title{2. Create Functions}
\p{Define functions that run in the cloud with the \code{\startverb @app.function()\stopverb} decorator.}

\pre{\startverb
@app.function()
def process_data(file_path: str):
    import pandas as pd
    df = pd.read_csv(file_path)
    return df.describe()
\stopverb}

\p{\strong{Call functions:}}

\pre{\startverb
# From local entrypoint
@app.local_entrypoint()
def main():
    result = process_data.remote("data.csv")
    print(result)
\stopverb}

\p{Run with: \code{\startverb modal run script.py\stopverb}}

\p{See \code{\startverb references/functions.md\stopverb} for function patterns, deployment, and parameter handling.}
}

\subtree{
\title{3. Request GPUs}
\p{Attach GPUs to functions for accelerated computation.}

\pre{\startverb
@app.function(gpu="H100")
def train_model():
    import torch
    assert torch.cuda.is_available()
    # GPU-accelerated code here
\stopverb}

\p{\strong{Available GPU types:}}

\ul{
\li{\code{\startverb T4\stopverb}, \code{\startverb L4\stopverb} - Cost-effective inference}
\li{\code{\startverb A10\stopverb}, \code{\startverb A100\stopverb}, \code{\startverb A100-80GB\stopverb} - Standard training/inference}
\li{\code{\startverb L40S\stopverb} - Excellent cost/performance balance (48GB)}
\li{\code{\startverb H100\stopverb}, \code{\startverb H200\stopverb} - High-performance training}
\li{\code{\startverb B200\stopverb} - Flagship performance (most powerful)}
}

\p{\strong{Request multiple GPUs:}}

\pre{\startverb
@app.function(gpu="H100:8")  # 8x H100 GPUs
def train_large_model():
    pass
\stopverb}

\p{See \code{\startverb references/gpu.md\stopverb} for GPU selection guidance, CUDA setup, and multi-GPU configuration.}
}

\subtree{
\title{4. Configure Resources}
\p{Request CPU cores, memory, and disk for functions.}

\pre{\startverb
@app.function(
    cpu=8.0,           # 8 physical cores
    memory=32768,      # 32 GiB RAM
    ephemeral_disk=10240  # 10 GiB disk
)
def memory_intensive_task():
    pass
\stopverb}

\p{Default allocation: 0.125 CPU cores, 128 MiB memory. Billing based on reservation or actual usage, whichever is higher.}

\p{See \code{\startverb references/resources.md\stopverb} for resource limits and billing details.}
}

\subtree{
\title{5. Scale Automatically}
\p{Modal autoscales functions from zero to thousands of containers based on demand.}

\p{\strong{Process inputs in parallel:}}

\pre{\startverb
@app.function()
def analyze_sample(sample_id: int):
    # Process single sample
    return result

@app.local_entrypoint()
def main():
    sample_ids = range(1000)
    # Automatically parallelized across containers
    results = list(analyze_sample.map(sample_ids))
\stopverb}

\p{\strong{Configure autoscaling:}}

\pre{\startverb
@app.function(
    max_containers=100,      # Upper limit
    min_containers=2,        # Keep warm
    buffer_containers=5      # Idle buffer for bursts
)
def inference():
    pass
\stopverb}

\p{See \code{\startverb references/scaling.md\stopverb} for autoscaling configuration, concurrency, and scaling limits.}
}

\subtree{
\title{6. Store Data Persistently}
\p{Use Volumes for persistent storage across function invocations.}

\pre{\startverb
volume = modal.Volume.from_name("my-data", create_if_missing=True)

@app.function(volumes={"/data": volume})
def save_results(data):
    with open("/data/results.txt", "w") as f:
        f.write(data)
    volume.commit()  # Persist changes
\stopverb}

\p{Volumes persist data between runs, store model weights, cache datasets, and share data between functions.}

\p{See \code{\startverb references/volumes.md\stopverb} for volume management, commits, and caching patterns.}
}

\subtree{
\title{7. Manage Secrets}
\p{Store API keys and credentials securely using Modal Secrets.}

\pre{\startverb
@app.function(secrets=[modal.Secret.from_name("huggingface")])
def download_model():
    import os
    token = os.environ["HF_TOKEN"]
    # Use token for authentication
\stopverb}

\p{\strong{Create secrets in Modal dashboard or via CLI:}}

\pre{\startverb
modal secret create my-secret KEY=value API_TOKEN=xyz
\stopverb}

\p{See \code{\startverb references/secrets.md\stopverb} for secret management and authentication patterns.}
}

\subtree{
\title{8. Deploy Web Endpoints}
\p{Serve HTTP endpoints, APIs, and webhooks with \code{\startverb @modal.web_endpoint()\stopverb}.}

\pre{\startverb
@app.function()
@modal.web_endpoint(method="POST")
def predict(data: dict):
    # Process request
    result = model.predict(data["input"])
    return {"prediction": result}
\stopverb}

\p{\strong{Deploy with:}}

\pre{\startverb
modal deploy script.py
\stopverb}

\p{Modal provides HTTPS URL for the endpoint.}

\p{See \code{\startverb references/web-endpoints.md\stopverb} for FastAPI integration, streaming, authentication, and WebSocket support.}
}

\subtree{
\title{9. Schedule Jobs}
\p{Run functions on a schedule with cron expressions.}

\pre{\startverb
@app.function(schedule=modal.Cron("0 2 * * *"))  # Daily at 2 AM
def daily_backup():
    # Backup data
    pass

@app.function(schedule=modal.Period(hours=4))  # Every 4 hours
def refresh_cache():
    # Update cache
    pass
\stopverb}

\p{Scheduled functions run automatically without manual invocation.}

\p{See \code{\startverb references/scheduled-jobs.md\stopverb} for cron syntax, timezone configuration, and monitoring.}
}
}

\subtree{
\title{Common Workflows}
\subtree{
\title{Deploy ML Model for Inference}
\pre{\startverb
import modal

# Define dependencies
image = modal.Image.debian_slim().uv_pip_install("torch", "transformers")
app = modal.App("llm-inference", image=image)

# Download model at build time
@app.function()
def download_model():
    from transformers import AutoModel
    AutoModel.from_pretrained("bert-base-uncased")

# Serve model
@app.cls(gpu="L40S")
class Model:
    @modal.enter()
    def load_model(self):
        from transformers import pipeline
        self.pipe = pipeline("text-classification", device="cuda")

    @modal.method()
    def predict(self, text: str):
        return self.pipe(text)

@app.local_entrypoint()
def main():
    model = Model()
    result = model.predict.remote("Modal is great!")
    print(result)
\stopverb}
}

\subtree{
\title{Batch Process Large Dataset}
\pre{\startverb
@app.function(cpu=2.0, memory=4096)
def process_file(file_path: str):
    import pandas as pd
    df = pd.read_csv(file_path)
    # Process data
    return df.shape[0]

@app.local_entrypoint()
def main():
    files = ["file1.csv", "file2.csv", ...]  # 1000s of files
    # Automatically parallelized across containers
    for count in process_file.map(files):
        print(f"Processed {count} rows")
\stopverb}
}

\subtree{
\title{Train Model on GPU}
\pre{\startverb
@app.function(
    gpu="A100:2",      # 2x A100 GPUs
    timeout=3600       # 1 hour timeout
)
def train_model(config: dict):
    import torch
    # Multi-GPU training code
    model = create_model(config)
    train(model)
    return metrics
\stopverb}
}
}

